{
  "answer": "**The third couplet (*sher*) of Allama Iqbal's ghazal in *Bang-e-Dara Part 1*, Chapter 5 (\"Kahoon kya aarzoo-e be-dili mujh ko kahan tak hai\") is:**\n\n> My sweet song is the fowler's prize, the garden's only light;  \n> And restless lightning's fury is my fragile nest's own chain.[^1]\n\n**In Urdu (original):**\n\n> چمن افروز ہے صياد ميري خوشنوائي تک  \n> رہي بجلي کي بے تابي ، سو ميرے آشياں تک ہے[^2]\n\n**In Roman transliteration:**\n\n> Chaman afroz hai sayyaad meri khush-nawaai tak  \n> Rahi bijli ki be-taabi, so mere aashiyaan tak hai[^3]\n\nThis is the third *sher* in the sequence of couplets, following the *matla* (first couplet) and the second *sher*. Each couplet ends with the refrain \"*tak hai*\". The translation is by *thothica*.[^1]\n\n[^1]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-e-Dara Part 1*, Ch. 5 (\"Kahoon kya aarzoo-e be-dili mujh ko kahan tak hai\"), [paragraph](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-1-55b25c/05-kahoon-kya-aarzoo-e-be-dili-mujh-ko-kahan-tak-hai/translation/#p-9ec149).\n\n[^2]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-e-Dara Part 1*, Ch. 5, [paragraph](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-1-55b25c/05-kahoon-kya-aarzoo-e-be-dili-mujh-ko-kahan-tak-hai/original/#p-677b77).\n\n[^3]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-e-Dara Part 1*, Ch. 5, [paragraph](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-1-55b25c/05-kahoon-kya-aarzoo-e-be-dili-mujh-ko-kahan-tak-hai/transliteration/#p-b8275d).",
